Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated).

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the spaghetti.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%grams}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once the bacon is golden, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and the onion. Cook until the mince has browned and the onion has softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Once the mince has browned, add the @finely chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1%carton}, @beef stock pot{1%pot} and the @water{100%ml} to the mince. Stir to combine, bring up to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer gently until the sauce has thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the Bolognese cooks, add the @spaghetti{180%grams} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{8%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back into the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the mince is cooked and the Bolognese has thickened, add the @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove the sauce from the heat and stir through the cooked spaghetti and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%grams}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} if it's a little too thick.

Share your speedy spag bol between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian style cheese to finish.

> Enjoy!